WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:13.722 --> 00:00:17.518
Listen. I just posted
a half a million in bail.

3
00:00:17.601 --> 00:00:19.728
- Ms. Buckley. I know you're frustrated--
- No. You know.

4
00:00:19.811 --> 00:00:21.647
<i>if I wanted to talk to paralegals.</i>

5
00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:25.317
<i>then I would've hired myself
a public defender. All right. Tom?</i>

6
00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:27.903
<i>For the amount of money
that I am paying y'all.</i>

7
00:00:27.986 --> 00:00:30.197
<i>I expect the top dog.</i>

8
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:32.658
Cat. not only is Lexi a senior associate.

9
00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:36.787
she's also the attorney I'd trust
if I were on trial for murder.

10
00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:39.998
- <i>Oh. yeah? I guess you know best.</i>
- [computer beeps]

11
00:00:42.084 --> 00:00:43.085
[scoffs]

12
00:00:43.168 --> 00:00:46.004
- [man chuckles] You wanna go swimming?
- Dad. who's in our yard?

13
00:00:46.088 --> 00:00:49.424
- [man] Come on. Get in the pool.
- Hang on just a sec. What?

14
00:00:49.508 --> 00:00:52.886
- You ain't seen nothing yet. baby.
- Ooh! Ooh. yeah.

15
00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:57.224
- I might let you fuck me in that pool.
- We can do whatever the fuck we want.

16
00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:59.017
- Go upstairs.
- [man laughing]

17
00:00:59.101 --> 00:01:00.978
- Sorry. y'all. I got to call you back.
- <i>Tom…</i>

18
00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:03.063
[ominous music playing]

19
00:01:10.279 --> 00:01:12.447
- You got another one of these. Trish?
- Mm-hmm.

20
00:01:13.031 --> 00:01:14.408
[Trish] You wanna move in?

21
00:01:15.576 --> 00:01:16.994
[man groans]

22
00:01:18.787 --> 00:01:22.207
Hey. man. God. it is a hot one. huh?

23
00:01:22.291 --> 00:01:23.667
What are you doing?

24
00:01:24.293 --> 00:01:27.212
- You know what they say…
- What do they say. Trish?

25
00:01:27.296 --> 00:01:29.464
They say it's not the heat.
it's the humidity.

26
00:01:29.548 --> 00:01:30.549
Yeah.

27
00:01:30.632 --> 00:01:34.386
[Trish] But. dang. those motherfuckers
are ganging up on us today.

28
00:01:34.469 --> 00:01:37.222
- [both chuckle]
- This is private property. Leave now.

29
00:01:37.306 --> 00:01:40.601
Hold on. We were invited.

30
00:01:40.684 --> 00:01:42.728
[Tom] By who?

31
00:01:42.811 --> 00:01:44.813
Well. by the-the homeowner. Tommy.

32
00:01:48.317 --> 00:01:51.195
- I'm Tom.
- [Trish giggling]

33
00:01:51.278 --> 00:01:53.030
Well. shit.

34
00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:55.908
You know. I guess
there must be two Toms then.

35
00:01:55.991 --> 00:01:58.285
[giggling continues]

36
00:01:58.368 --> 00:02:01.121
Oh. wait. wait. wait.
H-Hold on. all right?

37
00:02:01.205 --> 00:02:03.415
'Cause you're-you're not even
using your pool.

38
00:02:03.916 --> 00:02:05.876
That's a little selfish. don't you think?

39
00:02:05.959 --> 00:02:07.085
[Trish chuckles]

40
00:02:07.169 --> 00:02:10.380
We just wanna cool off. you know?
Some people don't have pools.

41
00:02:10.464 --> 00:02:12.341
Get the fuck outta here.

42
00:02:13.175 --> 00:02:14.551
Or what?

43
00:02:15.177 --> 00:02:17.012
Or I'm gonna take you apart.

44
00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:19.932
Gosh. Tom…

45
00:02:22.226 --> 00:02:24.561
You don't strike me as a violent guy.

46
00:02:32.528 --> 00:02:36.198
You know this is
a Stand Your Ground state. right?

47
00:02:37.699 --> 00:02:40.118
- Well. I guess we overstayed our welcome.
- Yeah.

48
00:02:40.869 --> 00:02:44.414
Trish… [clears throat] …round it up.

49
00:02:44.498 --> 00:02:45.958
- [Trish] Really?
- [grunts] Yeah.

50
00:02:46.041 --> 00:02:49.169
- [Trish] It's so pretty.
- I know. Another day. Come on.

51
00:02:49.253 --> 00:02:53.090
- Thanks for having us. [giggles]
- [laughing]

52
00:02:53.757 --> 00:02:55.968
- [grunts] It's heavy.
- You got it?

53
00:02:56.718 --> 00:02:58.053
So boring…

54
00:03:26.456 --> 00:03:30.586
[Ray] This is Zack's.
This is the mirror phone.

55
00:03:30.669 --> 00:03:33.839
Whatever's on Zack's cell
shows up here too.

56
00:03:34.464 --> 00:03:38.051
So I can text as Zack and then delete it.
and he won't see?

57
00:03:38.135 --> 00:03:40.721
You ever considered just talking to him?

58
00:03:41.346 --> 00:03:44.892
If he catches you doing that.
he's never gonna trust you again.

59
00:03:44.975 --> 00:03:46.894
Someone attacked him.

60
00:03:47.769 --> 00:03:50.772
- Drugged him and mutilated him.
- Hmm.

61
00:03:50.856 --> 00:03:53.108
I'm just doing what I need to do
to protect my son.

62
00:03:53.192 --> 00:03:54.276
Yeah.

63
00:03:57.821 --> 00:03:59.323
What are you not telling me?

64
00:04:01.325 --> 00:04:02.326
This girl…

65
00:04:03.577 --> 00:04:05.454
- This AngelX…
- Hmm.

66
00:04:07.331 --> 00:04:09.249
I think it's Max Cady.

67
00:04:10.501 --> 00:04:14.505
He is catfishing Zack
to fuck with Tom and me.

68
00:04:15.172 --> 00:04:17.632
- But you don't know for sure?
- Oh. I do.

69
00:04:17.716 --> 00:04:19.968
I do. I just… I can't prove it yet.

70
00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:24.556
Okay. Anna. I owe you everything.

71
00:04:25.474 --> 00:04:28.769
[stutters] If you hadn't stood up for me.
I'd still be rotting in prison

72
00:04:28.852 --> 00:04:31.146
- for a murder I didn't do.
- [sighs]

73
00:04:31.230 --> 00:04:33.524
But Max is going through
the same exact shit as me.

74
00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:35.442
- No.
- Look. you're going after a guy

75
00:04:35.526 --> 00:04:37.528
who was just exonerated.

76
00:04:37.611 --> 00:04:39.947
That goes against everything
SJLP stands for.

77
00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:41.615
No. I hear you. I do.

78
00:04:42.449 --> 00:04:44.284
But this is my family we're talking about.

79
00:04:44.368 --> 00:04:48.705
My advice. if you feel
he's really trying to get you…

80
00:04:48.789 --> 00:04:51.750
- He is.
- …then you play like you have his back.

81
00:04:52.668 --> 00:04:55.712
Work close with him. Earn his trust.

82
00:04:56.964 --> 00:04:59.132
Keep your friends close
and your enemies closer. right?

83
00:04:59.216 --> 00:05:01.635
[chuckles]
That's not exactly what I meant.

84
00:05:02.219 --> 00:05:04.763
I trust that you're gonna
keep this between us.

85
00:05:04.847 --> 00:05:06.765
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

86
00:05:15.274 --> 00:05:16.275
[safe beeps]

87
00:05:18.151 --> 00:05:19.152
Dad.

88
00:05:20.112 --> 00:05:22.114
Just a misunderstanding.

89
00:05:22.197 --> 00:05:23.699
What was the misunderstanding?

90
00:05:23.782 --> 00:05:24.867
Drunk.

91
00:05:25.367 --> 00:05:26.493
Wrong pool.

92
00:05:27.119 --> 00:05:28.662
Everything's fine.

93
00:05:28.745 --> 00:05:31.748
[grunting. panting]

94
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:45.470
[Noa] Centurion prison conglomerate
is going to settle restitution

95
00:05:45.554 --> 00:05:47.014
with Max this week.

96
00:05:47.097 --> 00:05:50.142
Good. They profit off pain.
they deserve to be spooked.

97
00:05:50.225 --> 00:05:52.060
Especially that warthog. Coburn.

98
00:05:52.144 --> 00:05:55.063
I hate his cologne.
and I really hate his neckties.

99
00:05:55.147 --> 00:05:57.399
[Noa] They're looking
to settle Cady's lawsuit.

100
00:05:57.482 --> 00:06:00.402
And he wants you to fly to Atlanta.
close the deal.

101
00:06:01.236 --> 00:06:03.614
He says you're the best lawyer he knows.

102
00:06:04.281 --> 00:06:07.451
I got him a life sentence.

103
00:06:07.534 --> 00:06:11.705
We get 40% and free publicity. Win-win.

104
00:06:12.664 --> 00:06:15.292
I know you had questions about Cady.

105
00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:17.753
[breathes deeply]
You can ask him on the trip.

106
00:06:17.836 --> 00:06:19.630
Wait. He's going?

107
00:06:22.049 --> 00:06:23.050
[sighs]

108
00:06:27.638 --> 00:06:28.639
Okay.

109
00:06:31.141 --> 00:06:32.142
Mmm.

110
00:06:39.650 --> 00:06:41.693
[chattering]

111
00:06:43.111 --> 00:06:45.614
Uh. nothing like ice cream on a hot day.

112
00:06:45.697 --> 00:06:48.492
- [chuckles] I knew it was you.
- Oh.

113
00:06:48.575 --> 00:06:50.369
Wendy Wilson. remember?

114
00:06:50.452 --> 00:06:52.371
Sorry to say I don't. No.

115
00:06:52.454 --> 00:06:53.914
I used to eat at your restaurant

116
00:06:53.997 --> 00:06:56.124
- at least once a week.
- Oh. okay.

117
00:06:56.208 --> 00:06:58.752
And it sure was sweet of you
to name it after your wife.

118
00:06:59.336 --> 00:07:02.756
When are you gonna open up
a new place for a girl to eat at?

119
00:07:05.551 --> 00:07:06.802
I don't know.

120
00:07:07.511 --> 00:07:08.929
Have a good one.

121
00:07:09.012 --> 00:07:12.474
Uh. hey. do you really think
Amy Brancato did it?

122
00:07:13.809 --> 00:07:16.770
Why would she wait
all these years to confess?

123
00:07:17.271 --> 00:07:18.272
Hmm.

124
00:07:18.897 --> 00:07:21.525
I'm starting to wonder if we do
know each other. Wendy.

125
00:07:21.608 --> 00:07:23.151
[both chuckle]

126
00:07:23.235 --> 00:07:25.988
I just… I think it had to be
a man. don't you?

127
00:07:26.738 --> 00:07:30.075
- Well…
- A man with strong hands.

128
00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:32.369
Speaking of…

129
00:07:33.412 --> 00:07:35.747
What? You like my hands?

130
00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:38.292
I can do a lot with these hands.

131
00:07:38.375 --> 00:07:40.043
- Oh. yeah? Like what?
- Oh. yeah. [chuckles]

132
00:07:41.879 --> 00:07:42.963
You really want to know?

133
00:07:44.006 --> 00:07:47.342
You know I grew up by a river? Yeah.

134
00:07:48.177 --> 00:07:52.639
We could go to a cabin by Cape Fear River.

135
00:07:53.599 --> 00:07:56.977
And I could catch a fish for you
with these hands.

136
00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:58.228
[both chuckle]

137
00:07:58.312 --> 00:08:04.776
And cook it with olive oil
and some garlic. Very simple.

138
00:08:04.860 --> 00:08:07.112
[sighs] That sounds mouthwatering.

139
00:08:07.196 --> 00:08:08.655
- [chuckles]
- Yeah.

140
00:08:08.739 --> 00:08:12.409
And then I could take you upstairs…

141
00:08:13.702 --> 00:08:15.787
[breathes deeply]

142
00:08:15.871 --> 00:08:17.873
…put my hand on your throat

143
00:08:17.956 --> 00:08:20.876
- and squeeze just a little bit.
- [moans]

144
00:08:20.959 --> 00:08:25.130
- Just enough. Would you like that?
- [breathes shakily] Yes.

145
00:08:25.214 --> 00:08:28.217
What if I choke you…

146
00:08:30.219 --> 00:08:32.888
- till you die. Wendy?
- No.

147
00:08:32.971 --> 00:08:34.515
- Would you like that?
- No.

148
00:08:34.597 --> 00:08:35.807
- Would you like that?
- [whimpers]

149
00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:39.602
- I bet you'd like that.
- [grunts. gasps]

150
00:08:40.854 --> 00:08:42.105
Nice to meet you.

151
00:08:44.358 --> 00:08:46.360
[deep house music playing]

152
00:08:47.069 --> 00:08:48.487
[knocks on door]

153
00:08:49.112 --> 00:08:50.239
Can we talk?

154
00:08:52.074 --> 00:08:53.867
[Zack] Uh. yeah. One sec.

155
00:08:56.954 --> 00:08:57.955
[music stops]

156
00:09:01.041 --> 00:09:02.042
Hi.

157
00:09:02.751 --> 00:09:04.294
I can have my phone back?

158
00:09:05.128 --> 00:09:10.425
Your dad and I just wanted to say
that we trust you and we love you.

159
00:09:15.264 --> 00:09:17.641
[Zack breathes deeply]

160
00:09:23.272 --> 00:09:28.318
<i>This man sits in jail for 17 years
while his white lady lawyer</i>

161
00:09:28.402 --> 00:09:31.029
<i>fucks the white prosecutor
and has his babies.</i>

162
00:09:31.738 --> 00:09:33.407
<i>They were obviously fucking already.</i>

163
00:09:33.490 --> 00:09:36.118
<i>They fucked him over.
The Bowdens need to go to jail.</i>

164
00:10:01.935 --> 00:10:03.020
[Natalie] Mom?

165
00:10:05.772 --> 00:10:07.232
Did you actually wear this?

166
00:10:07.316 --> 00:10:09.318
Where did you find that?

167
00:10:09.401 --> 00:10:11.028
The back of your closet.

168
00:10:11.111 --> 00:10:14.489
What are you doing rooting around
in my closet like a truffle pig?

169
00:10:14.573 --> 00:10:16.658
Well. I needed something for a party.

170
00:10:17.659 --> 00:10:19.328
What look were you going for?

171
00:10:19.995 --> 00:10:21.496
I have no idea.

172
00:10:21.997 --> 00:10:24.416
It was the '90s.
Nothing really made sense.

173
00:10:24.499 --> 00:10:26.710
Can't see you in this many ruffles.
[chuckles]

174
00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:29.046
Really? You can have it.

175
00:10:33.217 --> 00:10:35.844
Thanks. Mom.
I think Callie's gonna like this.

176
00:10:44.937 --> 00:10:46.021
[door closes]

177
00:11:10.921 --> 00:11:12.214
Fuck you. Max.

178
00:12:30.042 --> 00:12:31.084
[phone beeps]

179
00:12:44.723 --> 00:12:46.642
[country music playing on speaker]

180
00:12:52.314 --> 00:12:54.358
Breakfast for dinner. Good call.

181
00:12:56.401 --> 00:12:58.779
It's usually better
with orange soda though.

182
00:12:58.862 --> 00:13:01.573
The fuck are you doing? Who are you?

183
00:13:03.367 --> 00:13:04.576
I'm Anna.

184
00:13:04.660 --> 00:13:06.036
My name is "Fuck you."

185
00:13:11.875 --> 00:13:14.253
What the fuck are you doing. bitch?

186
00:13:29.142 --> 00:13:32.646
Well. um… Nevaeh…

187
00:13:33.981 --> 00:13:35.566
I'm Zack's mom.

188
00:13:36.525 --> 00:13:39.820
And I would like you to tell me
why he only has nine toes left.

189
00:13:40.445 --> 00:13:41.864
Why don't you ask him?

190
00:13:43.532 --> 00:13:46.034
He did it after he went home.
I wasn't even there.

191
00:13:49.329 --> 00:13:51.832
[breathes deeply]

192
00:13:51.915 --> 00:13:54.918
Okay. here's what you're gonna do.
You're gonna pick up that phone.

193
00:13:55.002 --> 00:13:56.461
you're gonna text Zack.

194
00:13:57.379 --> 00:13:58.589
- and break up with him.
- [sniffs]

195
00:13:59.464 --> 00:14:01.091
Be kind. but firm.

196
00:14:02.384 --> 00:14:04.636
I don't want any room for confusion.

197
00:14:08.223 --> 00:14:09.850
[chuckles]

198
00:14:09.933 --> 00:14:11.393
Don't fuck with me.

199
00:14:12.728 --> 00:14:14.479
I have friends in the Savannah PD.

200
00:14:14.563 --> 00:14:17.691
and I will have you arrested
for dealing drugs to a minor.

201
00:14:19.359 --> 00:14:21.403
I'll get you charged as an adult.

202
00:14:33.832 --> 00:14:34.833
[Nevaeh sniffs]

203
00:14:34.917 --> 00:14:36.168
[typing]

204
00:14:39.880 --> 00:14:41.048
[phone beeps]

205
00:14:44.927 --> 00:14:45.928
Happy?

206
00:14:49.306 --> 00:14:50.724
One more thing.

207
00:14:53.519 --> 00:14:54.937
Do you know who this is?

208
00:14:56.897 --> 00:14:59.107
Some old guy I'd definitely fuck.

209
00:15:00.108 --> 00:15:01.485
Now give me my shit back.

210
00:15:18.335 --> 00:15:20.003
If you need a place to stay.

211
00:15:20.796 --> 00:15:23.215
there's a shelter over on Fuller Street.

212
00:15:23.298 --> 00:15:26.510
It's safer than the one on Third
and they usually have available beds.

213
00:15:32.266 --> 00:15:35.561
[Tom] What were you thinking?
You're lucky it wasn't Max.

214
00:15:35.644 --> 00:15:38.021
And maybe you forgot
that the guy was in prison

215
00:15:38.105 --> 00:15:39.606
when Zack started talking to this girl.

216
00:15:39.690 --> 00:15:41.400
They have Internet in prison.

217
00:15:42.234 --> 00:15:43.986
What's going on with you?

218
00:15:44.903 --> 00:15:47.030
- You know you're spiraling. right?
- Yeah. I know.

219
00:15:47.114 --> 00:15:50.033
I know. I know. I can see the pattern.
I know that I am obsessing.

220
00:15:50.117 --> 00:15:53.412
But it's hard to stop
when I don't feel safe.

221
00:15:54.371 --> 00:15:56.373
Guess I can thank my dad for that.

222
00:15:57.124 --> 00:15:59.459
It's an unfortunate hand-me-down.

223
00:16:01.211 --> 00:16:06.758
You had a fight-or-flight childhood.
But that is not our reality.

224
00:16:08.969 --> 00:16:10.429
You're safe.

225
00:16:11.346 --> 00:16:13.473
We are safe.

226
00:16:13.557 --> 00:16:14.766
[sighs]

227
00:16:16.685 --> 00:16:17.686
Okay.

228
00:16:18.937 --> 00:16:21.565
Um. I was just trying to protect Zack.

229
00:16:21.648 --> 00:16:22.649
[sighs]

230
00:16:23.775 --> 00:16:25.110
But I should have told you.

231
00:16:27.613 --> 00:16:30.532
Next time. just let me know
if you're gonna go rogue.

232
00:16:30.616 --> 00:16:31.617
[chuckles]

233
00:16:32.284 --> 00:16:33.702
- All right?
- Yeah.

234
00:16:33.785 --> 00:16:34.953
- That's it.
- Okay.

235
00:16:35.746 --> 00:16:37.873
Guess it was just some feral teenager.

236
00:16:37.956 --> 00:16:39.666
[chuckles] Yeah.

237
00:16:39.750 --> 00:16:42.419
And now she's out of the picture.

238
00:16:42.503 --> 00:16:46.256
[water runs. stops]

239
00:16:54.389 --> 00:16:56.517
[brushing teeth]

240
00:16:58.477 --> 00:17:00.771
You sure you're gonna be okay
in the office without me for a day?

241
00:17:00.854 --> 00:17:04.398
[Noa] <i>You just get to Atlanta
and get us our 40% commission</i>

242
00:17:04.483 --> 00:17:06.484
- <i>and I'll stop freaking out.</i>
- I will do my best.

243
00:17:06.568 --> 00:17:07.736
<i>No pressure.</i>

244
00:17:09.780 --> 00:17:11.531
[person laughing]

245
00:17:21.083 --> 00:17:23.585
Pinch the blade at the base.

246
00:17:23.669 --> 00:17:26.964
Straight down like a guillotine.

247
00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:30.968
There. That's great.

248
00:17:31.051 --> 00:17:32.761
